  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Citizen Action in Anti-Corruption</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will provide independent analysis of circumstances of the impact of corruption on people&apos;s lives from which clear anti -corruption messages will be generated with emphasis on enabling and facilitating a culture of anti -corruption action by citizens. The message will be simplified yet made to remain powerful empirical evidence on the economic and social costs of corruption.  The messages will be packaged and shared with the public to make knowledge/information more readily available for mass mobilisation against corruption through; Radio Listening Clubs; Social media such as WhatsApp and Facebook; Oxfam will partner with two key mobile phone providers to share the information with the public through SMS and provide a text message hotline.</narrative>
  </description>
